Maxima wanted to add more to her bark at Rodimus but didn't. As Hydras spoke 
up, she back off to stand beside him. Things would correct itself from her end 
luckily... & hopefully, stay that way. She was tired of loosing her comrades. 
& frankly, she feared loosing Hydras. 

Her crimson optics only watched Rodimus for a moment, to watch his response 
to Hydras' words. She would talk to Rodimus in due time, & in private 
concerning another issue. 

But for now, she would stand at Hydras' side.

--part1_1e4.b75cc22.2c229d44_boundary
